    <name>
				<text>35.3.1.4 Balls from a bag</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
A bag contains \(20\) balls, \({@aa@}\) are coloured red, \({@bb@}\) are coloured green, \({@cc@}\) are coloured blue, \({@dd@}\) are coloured white and \({@ee@}\) are coloured yellow.  One ball is selected at random.  Find the probabilities of the following events.<p><br>
</p><ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>The ball is either red or green. [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>The ball is not blue. [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li><li><p>The ball is either red or white or blue.&nbsp; (Hint: consider the complementary event.) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li></ol><p></p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>A bag contains \(20\) balls, \({@aa@}\) are coloured red, \({@bb@}\) are coloured green, \({@cc@}\) are coloured blue, \({@dd@}\) are coloured white and \({@ee@}\) are coloured yellow.&nbsp;<br></p><p>Note that a ball has only one colour, designated by the letters \(R,G,B,W,Y\).</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>\(\text{P}(R\cup G)=\text{P}(R)+\text{P}(G) = \dfrac{{@aa@}}{20}+\dfrac{{@bb@}}{20} = \displaystyle {@ta1@}.\)&nbsp;</p></li>

<li><p>\(\text{P}(B')=1-\text{P}(B)=1-\dfrac{{@cc@}}{20} = \displaystyle {@ta2@}.\)</p></li><li><p></p><p>The complementary event is \(G\cup Y\),&nbsp; \(\text{P}(G\cup Y) = \dfrac{{@bb@}}{20}+\dfrac{{@ee@}}{20}.\)</p><p>Hence \(\text{P}(R\cup W\cup B)=1-\text{P}(G\cup Y) = \displaystyle {@ta3@}\).</p></li></ol>
<p><br></p>
In part c) we could alternatively have used an obvious extension of the law of addition
for mutually exclusive events:&nbsp;<p>\[\text{P}(R\cup W\cup B)=\text{P}(R)+\text{P}(W)+\text{P}(B)=\frac{{@aa@}}{20}+\frac{{@cc@}}{20}+\frac{{@dd@}}{20}={@ta3@}.\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
